description.narrative: Government at highest level committed to making available statistically sound and internationally comparable data on children and women .The National Centre for Child Welfare led the update of the situation analysis using a life-cycle and human-rights approach, including voices of children and adolescents for the first time. The government committed to strengthen the national mechanism and initiate institutional reform as per recommendations of the evaluation of the Justice for Children programme. By mid-2020, the ongoing Mid Term Review of the Government of Sudan- UNICEF Country Programme will have concluded ensuring that it remains relevant to emerging opportunities and priorities | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:31/12/2019
